http://mathscinotes.wordpress.com/2011/03/28/battery-state-of-charge/
State of charge % vs voltage at battery load- you can go to 50% with a 
deep cycle, with a starting battery you can go to 80% left, so that is 
about 12v running a 3 amp load, probably typical for a light and TV/dvd 
player- depends on wattage total= watts divided by 12v=amps drawn.
